title: A bit more about me outside of academia …
Laura Bumbulis
text:
Welcome! I’m a second-year PhD Candidate in Statistics at the University of Waterloo, working under the supervision of Professor Richard Cook. I completed my BMath in 2022 and my MMath in Statistics in 2024, both also at the University of Waterloo.
My research interests involve multistate modelling under complex observation schemes as well as two-phase designs for failure time studies.
